{"key":"processedPost-7184902","value":{"id":7184902,"first":7184317,"last":7185544,"when":1184638429,"utime":"07/17/07 05:13 AM","content":"A good CO2 meter is $5K, so forget it unless you're rich.  Those of us who have had access to one have already laid out the air exchange requirements for mushrooms anyway.<br />The best place in my experience to get an analog hygrometer is from a local cigar shop.  Find the high end cigar shop in your area.  They'll have good ones for sale.  Some dude with $20,000 worth of cigars wants his humidor dialed in properly.<br />You don't need a thermometer.  If you're comfortable in a t-shirt, your mushrooms will be too.  If not, adjust heat or AC as required.<br />RR","title":"Re: Need help finding a good RH Meter, Thermomiter, and Co2 Meter for my fruiting chamber..."}}